    "summary": "Currently pursuing a Master's degree in Governance for Development, with a passion for unraveling the intricacies of policy translation in water management projects from the Netherlands to Colombia.\n\n\ud83d\udd0d Leveraging extensive experience as a researcher in Colombia, I specialize in using Applied Research Methods and co-creation tools to monitor and evaluate the implementation of policies. My work focuses on bridging the gap between policy makers, Afro-Colombian communities, and youth, co-creating solutions from grassroots perspectives while identifying the limitations to effective policy implementation.\n\n\ud83c\udf0d My journey has taken me deep into ethnographic approaches in both Colombia and M\u00e9xico, exploring the dynamics of participation, identity, and displacement. These experiences have enriched my understanding of the human element in policy, allowing me to connect with diverse communities and drive positive change.",
